Your task: {{.TaskName}}
Task file: {{.TaskPath}}
Project file: {{.ProjectPath}}
Workspace: {{.Workspace}}

Read the task description in the task file and complete the work inside this
workspace. The workspace already contains the repos listed in the project
file, all on branch `{{.Branch}}`. Make whatever code changes the task
description requires.

When done, edit the task file to set `status: success` (or `status: failed`
with a `failure_reason` if you cannot complete it). The daemon will trigger
the commit agent on success and will restart the task on failure (up to a
limit). Do not commit, push, or change `.project.yaml` — that is the
daemon's and commit agent's job.

The task's `status:` field is a fixed enum — any other value is rejected
by the daemon and your save won't take effect. Valid: `ready`,
`running`, `success`, `failed`, `blocked`, `committed`. For *your* exit:
use `success` (work done) or `failed` (couldn't complete). Do not
invent values like `active`, `done`, or `complete`.
